# Identification arithmetic for separating F3 (across-issuer reallocation) from
# F4 (across-holder dollar-leg run) on a SINGLE cross-sectional 13x14 grid.
#
# Observed object available to a single-snapshot factor model:
#   the 13x14 matrix X (one realization). A factor model on a SINGLE matrix can
#   only be identified via STRUCTURE IMPOSED on loadings, not via a sample
#   covariance over repeated draws -- there is exactly ONE draw.
#
# Two routes a factor model could use for cross-sectional identification:
#  (R1) cross-HOLDER covariance: treat the 14 issuer columns as "variables" and
#       the (<=13) holders as observations -> Sigma_col is 14x14, rank <= 13-1=12.
#  (R2) cross-ISSUER covariance: treat 13 holders as "variables", 14 issuers as
#       observations -> Sigma_row is 13x13, rank <= 14-1=13.
#
# F4 = a COMMON DOLLAR-LEG factor: loads on the USA column across holders. In R1
#      it is a single column's loading vector. In a single snapshot, "the USA
#      column is high/low across holders" cannot be separated from "holders differ
#      in total size" (a holder fixed effect) UNLESS a scale normalization
#      (shares) removes the size factor.
# F3 = a SUBSTITUTION factor: within-row reallocation across issuer columns,
#      i.e. negative covariance between a holder's USA share and its share in
#      destination issuer k.
#
# The separating restriction needs: variation that moves USA-column loadings
# ACROSS holders (F4) ORTHOGONAL to variation that moves the WITHIN-row issuer
# split (F3). On a single snapshot these are read off the SAME Sigma. They are
# separately identified ONLY IF there is a second issuer column whose
# cross-holder pattern is moved by F4 but NOT by F3 (an exclusion), AND a
# destination column moved by F3 but NOT F4.
print("Single-snapshot 13x14 grid: 1 realization, NOT a panel.")
print("Order condition for an UNRESTRICTED 2-factor decomposition of one matrix:")
print("  a single matrix has rank <= min(13,14)=13; its SVD gives 13 orthogonal")
print("  components but their ROTATION is unidentified without external restriction.")
print("  -> F3 and F4 are two directions in that rotation-indeterminate subspace.")
print("  Separating them REQUIRES an a-priori loading restriction (exclusion/sign).")
EOF
